<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-930-282  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 930 282.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  Nov 1989 v26 n11 p24(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>USTA, hotel, town pull together after quake.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gitlin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The United States Telephone Association (USTA) convention met inSan Francisco during the earthquake in 1989.andP;  Because ofpreplanning, nearly all attendees could call home.andP;  Phone servicestill operated smoothly due to computerized network monitoring andre-routing, emergency drills, reinforced flooring and equipmentbraces at COs, and an extra 25 feet of fiber-optic cable in eachrun.andP;  Guests at hotels kept their phone calls short, often callingone person to contact others.andP;  The quake downed the hotel computersystem, but USTA members that checked out were assured that theirbills would be mailed to them.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Pacific Bell (planning).andO;Topic:     United States Telephone AssociationDisaster PlanningDisaster RecoveryTelecommunicationsTelephone CompaniesTelephone Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>